1
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:19,199
Meiduo, how long are you gonna stare at it?

2
00:00:19,199 --> 00:00:20,920
I've already poked three ant nests.

3
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,039
Hush, I'm counting its tree rings.

4
00:00:23,399 --> 00:00:24,160
What's a tree ring?

5
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:24,920
Can you eat it?

6
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:26,760
For every year a tree grows,

7
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:28,079
it draws a circle inside its belly.

8
00:00:28,519 --> 00:00:31,519
My dad says this tree is 1,000 years old.

9
00:00:31,519 --> 00:00:33,079
I'm wondering if there are

10
00:00:33,079 --> 00:00:34,600
a thousand circles in its belly.

11
00:00:37,119 --> 00:00:38,399
Well, can you see them?

12
00:00:38,399 --> 00:00:39,079
No, I can't.

13
00:00:39,759 --> 00:00:40,799
Then how do you know?

14
00:00:41,079 --> 00:00:42,719
I'm just guessing. You wouldn't get it.

15
00:00:55,039 --> 00:00:56,960
Zaxi, look at that pretty mushroom!

16
00:00:58,479 --> 00:00:59,759
Where? Where? Where?

17
00:00:59,759 --> 00:01:00,359
Right here.

18
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:04,879
So pretty!

19
00:01:05,359 --> 00:01:06,840
I'm gonna pick it.

20
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:08,280
No, you can't.

21
00:01:08,799 --> 00:01:09,920
Why not?

22
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:12,079
My dad says mushrooms are for eating.

23
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,760
This isn't an ordinary mushroom.

24
00:01:13,760 --> 00:01:15,239
It's a Reishi mushroom, a medicinal herb.

25
00:01:15,359 --> 00:01:17,359
Medicinal herbs are for eating too.

26
00:01:18,519 --> 00:01:19,599
Zaxi!

27
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:22,640
Meiduo, look, it looks really tasty.

28
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:23,280
If you pick it,

29
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,359
it'll die.

30
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,359
I'll give you half.

31
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:27,280
I don't want it.

32
00:01:29,079 --> 00:01:30,439
Meiduo, wait for me!

33
00:01:30,719 --> 00:01:32,120
I'll give you the whole thing!

34
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:33,640
Meiduo, wait for me!

35
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,639
Meiduo, you've been away for three years.

36
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:42,639
You must've missed home.

37
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:43,960
I did.

38
00:02:44,639 --> 00:02:45,840
I dreamed of coming back.

39
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:49,240
The village roads are so nice now.

40
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:49,960
Yeah.

41
00:02:50,159 --> 00:02:51,800
Our village is a key focus now.

42
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:54,960
I hear they're building an Ecological Demonstration Zone.

43
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:57,879
That's the project I brought back with me.

44
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:00,719
Everyone in the village has been talking,

45
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:03,240
saying the Pride of the village is back.

46
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:05,199
Coming back with technology.

47
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:06,919
To lead everyone to prosperity.

48
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,960
Uncle Suolang, don't say that.

49
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,520
I'm just doing

50
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,800
what I'm supposed to do.

51
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:17,719
Come on, come on.

52
00:03:17,919 --> 00:03:18,759
Hold the Khata up higher.

53
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,120
Look sharp, everyone.

54
00:03:21,759 --> 00:03:23,919
Our Chinese Academy of Sciences Doctor.

55
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,800
We need to do this properly, okay?

56
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,240
Okay.

57
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,159
Party Secretary.

58
00:03:28,439 --> 00:03:29,240
Your back hasn't healed yet.

59
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:31,280
Why don't I welcome her instead?

60
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,599
My back's fine, just a minor injury.

61
00:03:33,919 --> 00:03:35,400
Meiduo is the pride of our village.

62
00:03:35,439 --> 00:03:36,400
I had to come.

63
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,039
Alright.

64
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,360
Why isn't she here yet?

65
00:03:41,719 --> 00:03:42,280
She's here!

66
00:03:43,039 --> 00:03:43,919
Line up, line up!

67
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,439
Where's the Doctor?

68
00:03:56,199 --> 00:03:57,960
She insisted on stopping by the road.

69
00:03:58,280 --> 00:03:59,800
Said she had to check some data.

70
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:01,680
Grabbed her bag and went into the forest.

71
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,159
Told me to bring the equipment back.

72
00:04:07,319 --> 00:04:08,039
Professor, look.

73
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:10,960
This is the mother plant I planted

74
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:11,840
myself three years ago.

75
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,199
The density is just perfect.

76
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,120
Greenhouses can't grow anything this wild.

77
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:23,560
As long as we collect this spore powder,

78
00:04:23,839 --> 00:04:25,160
we can mass-produce the strongest

79
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:25,879
first-generation seedlings.

80
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,759
Okay, I'll start collecting then.

81
00:04:29,759 --> 00:04:30,199
Goodbye.

82
00:04:44,879 --> 00:04:45,519
Good girl.

83
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:47,879
Not a single bit can be lost.

84
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,560
This is the village's hope for next year.

85
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:17,519
You can't just pick things here.

86
00:05:17,519 --> 00:05:18,680
This is our protected forest.

87
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,439
Keep quiet.

88
00:05:21,199 --> 00:05:22,040
You're disturbing the airflow.

89
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:24,839
I have a collection permit. It's all legal.

90
00:05:28,279 --> 00:05:28,839
Who is it?

91
00:05:29,399 --> 00:05:29,959
You!

92
00:05:31,319 --> 00:05:31,920
Zaxi.

93
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:33,360
So you do recognize me.

94
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,680
Doctor Meiduo, long time no see.

95
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,160
Give it back.

96
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,680
Three minutes off the mother plant,

97
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:39,800
they'll be ruined by contaminating bacteria.

98
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,199
Then I can't do the sterile culture.

99
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:42,160
The rule in the mountains is,

100
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,560
whoever picks it first gets to keep it.

101
00:05:45,519 --> 00:05:46,079
You know what?

102
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:46,800
This isn't just an ordinary one.

103
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,000
Jimei's stone pot chicken

104
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:48,879
is just missing this one ingredient.

105
00:05:48,879 --> 00:05:50,839
Otherwise it tastes like dishwater.

106
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:51,399
What did you say?

107
00:05:52,279 --> 00:05:53,319
You're using it to stew chicken?

108
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:54,600
That's making the most of it.

109
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,759
Pity to leave such good stuff in the wild.

110
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,079
No time to chat. I'm heading back.

111
00:05:58,279 --> 00:05:58,839
Zaxi!

112
00:05:58,839 --> 00:05:59,600
Pack up your stuff.

113
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,439
I'll share a bowl of soup with you.

114
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:05,040
Zaxi!

115
00:06:06,759 --> 00:06:07,560
Zaxi!

116
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:10,519
Zaxi! Zaxi!

117
00:06:10,519 --> 00:06:11,680
Zaxi, wait for me!

118
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,600
Meiduo, hurry up!

119
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,639
Chicken soup goes bad if stewed too long.

120
00:06:16,439 --> 00:06:17,160
Zaxi!

121
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:19,399
That's a seedling, not a seasoning!

122
00:06:20,959 --> 00:06:23,120
Zaxi! Zaxi!

123
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:29,000
Meiduo, wait for me!

124
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,480
No way, Meiduo!

125
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:32,279
I said I'd give you half!

126
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:34,839
Zaxi!

127
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:41,000
Meiduo! Meiduo!

128
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:44,959
Zaxi!

129
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,639
Zaxi, stop running!

130
00:06:47,639 --> 00:06:48,720
Hurry up, Meiduo!

131
00:07:04,399 --> 00:07:05,720
Jimei!

132
00:07:07,639 --> 00:07:08,680
Jimei!

133
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:10,399
Jimei!

134
00:07:10,399 --> 00:07:11,160
Quick, quick, quick!

135
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,360
Look, look at this!

136
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:12,720
Okay.

137
00:07:15,639 --> 00:07:16,120
How is it?

138
00:07:17,879 --> 00:07:18,639
Not too sweet, not too salty.

139
00:07:19,079 --> 00:07:20,800
Just a bit stifled after being cooked.

140
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,600
Look at this, Jimei.

141
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,439
The flesh is firm.

142
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:28,279
Zaxi, where did you find it?

143
00:07:28,759 --> 00:07:30,759
It grew in the mountains for over 3 years.

144
00:07:30,759 --> 00:07:32,079
Right, so hurry up and stew it.

145
00:07:32,079 --> 00:07:32,639
Wait.

146
00:07:34,199 --> 00:07:35,839
Judging by the pattern, it's not wild.

147
00:07:36,399 --> 00:07:37,560
This was artificially cultivated.

148
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:40,879
That's strange.

149
00:07:41,199 --> 00:07:42,680
I saw it myself in the forest.

150
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,600
Who cares if it's wild

151
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,360
or cultivated?

152
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,319
It's just a mushroom, isn't it?

153
00:07:46,319 --> 00:07:46,879
Come on, come on.

154
00:07:46,879 --> 00:07:47,800
Let's stew it first.

155
00:08:01,079 --> 00:08:02,680
Zaxi, Zaxi.

156
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:04,839
Uncle Jimei.

157
00:08:05,079 --> 00:08:06,519
Meiduo, have a seat.

158
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:08,120
Meiduo, the soup will be ready soon.

159
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:08,839
Have a taste.

160
00:08:14,839 --> 00:08:15,920
That Reishi mushroom from earlier...

161
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:17,959
Is it in this pot of soup?

162
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,079
Yes.

163
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:20,959
Just put it in. It smells great.

164
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,120
Do you know what that was?

165
00:08:24,639 --> 00:08:25,560
A Reishi mushroom, obviously.

166
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,839
I domesticated it in the wild for years.

167
00:08:28,839 --> 00:08:29,600
It's a highly resistant mother plant.

168
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:32,000
Seed source for natural spore propagation.

169
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:34,360
For the village's 300-acre under-forest base,

170
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,360
I brought back this seedling.

171
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:36,720
Seedling?

172
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,240
The spores I was going to collect

173
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:46,159
could mass-produce the strongest first-gen seedlings.

174
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:47,519
With it,

175
00:08:47,519 --> 00:08:49,159
the village could build the under-forest base,

176
00:08:49,519 --> 00:08:51,840
apply for an Ecological Demonstration Zone,

177
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,480
and have a chance to get support funds.

178
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,320
Support funds...

179
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:56,799
Now look what you've done.

180
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,159
The mother plant is cooked.

181
00:08:59,159 --> 00:08:59,840
The spores are dead.

182
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,399
The funds are gone too.

183
00:09:02,399 --> 00:09:04,000
I didn't know it was a seedling!

184
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,399
I thought it just grew in the wild.

185
00:09:05,399 --> 00:09:06,360
You're the one who grew up in the wild!

186
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:08,080
Just because it's in the wild, you pick it?

187
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,120
Just because it's in the wild, you stew it?

188
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:09,960
Meiduo, Meiduo.

189
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:10,759
Here's the thing.

190
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,320
I told Zaxi to go up the mountain for mushrooms.

191
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:14,720
As for this Reishi mushroom,

192
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,960
I cut it, I stewed it.

193
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:17,799
If you want to blame someone, blame me.

194
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:19,559
Uncle Jimei, I'm not blaming you.

195
00:09:19,679 --> 00:09:20,200
I...

196
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:37,759
What's your name?

197
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:40,639
Zaxi. You know that.

198
00:09:40,639 --> 00:09:42,039
I mean your full name.

199
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:43,919
I'm putting it in the incident report.

200
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:46,159
18,000 in direct losses,

201
00:09:46,159 --> 00:09:48,039
plus indirect support funds losses.

202
00:09:48,039 --> 00:09:49,159
Someone has to take responsibility.

203
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:50,799
18,000?

204
00:09:51,759 --> 00:09:53,039
This pot of soup costs 18,000?

205
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:54,559
18,000.

206
00:09:54,559 --> 00:09:55,720
Gene sequencing cost,

207
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,120
field monitoring equipment depreciation,

208
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,320
plus manual cultivation fees.

209
00:09:58,559 --> 00:10:00,279
Not counting my intellectual cost.

210
00:10:00,639 --> 00:10:02,279
A conservative estimate is around 18,000.

211
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:03,440
Oh, by the way,

212
00:10:03,759 --> 00:10:05,519
the support funds are the village's money.

213
00:10:05,519 --> 00:10:06,960
Go tell the Party Secretary yourself.

214
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:08,759
I...

215
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,279
Uncle Jimei, I'm heading off.

216
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:12,919
Drop by sometime.

217
00:10:13,399 --> 00:10:13,960
Oh, and...

218
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:16,679
You'd better finish this whole pot of soup,

219
00:10:16,679 --> 00:10:17,440
down to the last drop.

220
00:10:17,679 --> 00:10:18,480
After all, it's expensive.

221
00:10:21,039 --> 00:10:21,799
Meiduo!

222
00:10:23,279 --> 00:10:23,720
Bro.

223
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:25,039
I think this pot of soup

224
00:10:25,679 --> 00:10:26,320
is quite something.

225
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,240
What's so special?

226
00:10:29,919 --> 00:10:31,279
Come on, drink up.

227
00:10:31,519 --> 00:10:33,840
18,000 is a bit pricey.

228
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:36,639
How can I bear to drink such pricey soup?

229
00:10:36,639 --> 00:10:37,600
Drink it while it's hot.

230
00:10:43,279 --> 00:10:44,519
Still feeling stifled?

231
00:10:44,879 --> 00:10:45,799
Even more stifled now.

232
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:50,559
Um...

233
00:10:50,799 --> 00:10:52,840
What are you guys making? Smells great!

234
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:53,879
Smells good, huh?

235
00:10:54,879 --> 00:10:55,440
It's poison.

236
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:57,919
Poison smells this good?

237
00:11:05,559 --> 00:11:06,240
Zaxi.

238
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,519
Let me taste it for you.

239
00:11:07,879 --> 00:11:09,039
I'm a Dianping

240
00:11:09,039 --> 00:11:09,879
V8 Member, you know.

241
00:11:09,879 --> 00:11:10,919
My sense of taste is super sharp.

242
00:11:15,639 --> 00:11:16,159
This, this, this...

243
00:11:16,159 --> 00:11:17,120
This is incredibly delicious!

244
00:11:18,279 --> 00:11:20,759
This 18,000 soup really is something else.
